# Pre-launch reminders (Nabad)

## Song lifecycle — DECIDED: local-first (TikTok-style)

Samy confirmed (Jun 30 2026) the final model is **local-first**. Private songs
live only on the device they were made on; the cloud is reached **only when the
user publishes**. (Shipped in commit `821b135` "Go local-first for songs to stop
deleted songs resurrecting".) Not deferred anymore — treat this as the policy.

**Behavior:**
- Private songs: local library only — **NOT** inserted into `user_songs`. The audio is still archived to `song_archive` + cover saved, so the draft keeps playing locally even after the Suno CDN link expires and publishing later is instant. Because there is no cloud row, private songs do **not** sync to other devices, a reinstall/new phone won't have them, and deleting is permanent (this is what fixed the "deleted songs resurrecting" bug).
- Published songs: publish is the **only** path that writes to the cloud (`user_songs`, `public_on_profile`) — kept permanently, sync to any signed-in device, and show on the public profile + Discover.
- No Nabad-imposed delete on private songs.

**Product line:** *Publish = Nabad keeps it forever and on every device. Private = only on this device; publish to keep it safe.*

**Coach alignment:** `api/_lib/coach-knowledge.js` was updated (Jun 30) to state this explicitly. Keep it in sync if the policy ever changes.

**Revisit at scale when:** users ask for a "back up all my drafts" option, or pricing tiers need "backup library" vs "publish to keep".

---

## Song/storage items worth doing before launch (recommended)

1. **Archive reliability** — ensure `/api/songs/archive` runs after generation; surface clear UI if play fails (expired Suno link, archive failed), not silent broken Play
2. **Publish = permanent** — on publish, archive must succeed (or retry) before showing public; never rely on Suno URL for published posts
3. **Profile counts aligned** — stats Songs pill, Posts tab, and public `#/u/` profile must use same cloud public count (owner = visitor)
4. **Broken-link UX** — grey chip or toast: "This draft expired — publish next time to keep it on Nabad"
5. **Optional backfill** — one pass to archive old library rows still on Suno-only URLs

---

## Explicitly out of scope for v1 launch (unless asked)

- Auto-delete private songs after 15 days
- Discover survival / score expiry (paused in app)
- Paid "backup entire library" tier
- Storage cleanup on delete (orphaned `song_archive` files)

When user asks "what do we have to do before launch?", lead with the **recommended** list above and note **deferred** lifecycle decision.
